metadata.name: Accalance 1 #123
metadata.description:
This work is an investigation into the visual weight of colors and based on preliminary research results.

Each piece is based on an accented analogous color scheme and displays a range of hues arranged around a single primary color, balanced them with a complimentary colored "accent object". An algorithm varies the size of the fields and their lightness to keep the composition in balance. The primary color is denoted by one out of 24 color tables, there are four different paper stocks and the accent object can have three shapes: circle (75%), diamond (20%) and hexagon (5%).

I view this as a celebration of stability and harmony in unquiet times. To me, these compositions almost have a meditative quality: Looking at them makes me feel at ease and content.

Rendered in high resolution (4800x6000px). Keys:

f: final composite artwork
a: artwork without the legend
l : only the legend
o: outline mode
d: description of the features (console)
s: saves in high-resolution (4800x6000px)
c: copyright notice (console)

metadata.name: How Moons Are Made #2
metadata.description:
As a collector of 'How Moons Are Made' you are in control over the work's composition and colors. Your control is deliberately constrained so that the space to explore remains overseeable. 

I wanted to create an intuitive and playful way to explore a generative system that still allows for rich variation in a coherent collection. I hope collectors enjoy their explorations and find their favorite corners of the system. Let's find out how moons are made.

The work uses a custom interface that has two modes. One to change the overall composition by dragging around nodes. The other to explore different color palettes and variety in decoration.

The final minted version will come out identical to the composition you created.

Commands for the minted version:
f = fullscreen toggle
s = save image at screen resolution
2 = save image at print size DIN A2 at 300 dpi
1 = save image at print size DIN A1 at 300 dpi
0 = save image at print size DIN A0 at 300 dpi

metadata.name: TRACE #69
metadata.description:
Introducing TRACE, an ingenious generative art project that weaves magic from the mesmerizing movement trajectories of the most fundamental geometric shapes, such as lines and arcs. Prepare to be captivated as we delve into the intricate interplay of geometry, motion, and filters, culminating in stunning and unpredictable still images. Much like life's unexpected encounters, stories, and moments, the final results remain veiled until the very last second, keeping us enthralled in a realm of perpetual wonder.

The name TRACE holds a twofold significance, each contributing to the essence of this remarkable creation. 

Firstly, at its core, TRACE is an amalgamation of diverse geometric trajectories, intricately intertwined to form an artistic masterpiece. The fusion of shapes and movements sets the stage for an awe-inspiring visual journey that unfolds with every stroke.

Secondly, and more profoundly, TRACE embodies the very essence of life's rich tapestry. Every individual, event, object, or fleeting moment that graces our existence leaves an indelible mark, a trace of its presence. These traces become the threads that weave our personal histories, forming the tapestry of our lives. Just like cherished treasures, the images composed of these past experiences are unique and invaluable, revealing the essence of who we are.

----・----・----・----・----・----・----・----・----・----・----・----

Save as a Picture:

Press “s”or “S” to download a PNG copy of the artwork.

metadata.name: flow | meditations #189
metadata.description:
"flow | meditations" is part of the live outdoor art installation - 'Computational Convergence' at India Art Fair, held from 9-12 February 2023 in New Delhi.

To flow is to expand and contract with the waves within. A tangled chaos of particles is unhindered with a deep breath and relaxation. With permission to flow, patterns emerge.

To meditate with this artwork:
- keep your eyes moving slowly, trying not to fixate on a point.
- when thoughts arise, gently let them go and return to the artwork.
- bring your awareness again, to the act of seeing moment by moment.

Flow might arise in many ways- turbulent, synchronous, circular, ephemeral, convergent, divergent, rising, waning or a mix of any of these.

[GPU-intensive, Best viewed @ 4k/full-screen. 'j' for screencap, 'v' to toggle video recording.]

metadata.name: RedSplat #3
metadata.description:
This artwork is a digital collage and image compositing that utilizes a combination of computer-generated imagery (CGI) and artificial intelligence.
The layering and random placement of elements create an image that is unique and divergent from what a human artist might create.

The final composition is achieved through the use of a custom-written javascript program that I wrote in pure javascript, which allows for the layers to be placed together randomly

========
If you see this NFT on OBJKT this is a generative art minted on FXhash.com
========

metadata.name: When we were Kids #5
metadata.description:
When we were kids.

A work that goes back to our childhood.
When I was a kid I loved spending time with my grandmother and parents, we took a lot of walks with them, looked at different houses, spent time in nature, painted and in general were very much involved in the creative component, it was my parents and grandmother who instilled in me a love for creativity.

Probably one of the few things that have survived to these days is my childhood drawings, a little funny, sloppy, but so real and sincere.

In this work I wanted to take me back to those carefree times and remember with what eagerness and zeal I tried every day to learn something new or to go further than before.

None of this would have happened without my family, for which I am truly grateful.

10% of primary sales will be donated to Cure Parkinson's, I hope all children will have a childhood where they can spend time with their loved ones.

Be patient, some variations take a little longer to render.

Press S for Save Canvas as PNG.

By aleks.ustya, @ALEKUSTN. Made with p5js.

metadata.name: Sketches:Pairs of Tails:Majestic Creatures #29
metadata.description:
Addendum to Annuls of WorSAGE (the Worshipful Society of Adventurers and Generative Explorers) XXVII.Vol.2048

There is a significantly common phenomena in which Pairs of "Tails of Majestic Creatures" are found together. Various sketches of these "Pairs" have been collated and are available, free of charge, the collectors of the initial Tails of Majestic Creatures collection based upon a recently taken collection registry snapshot. 

These sketches are available on a one per collector basis and for a limited time only after which they will no longer be accessible.

The sketches come in 2 forms - an ink and color style, and a pencil style - for which different colored paper has been used.

The digitally minded can press s to get a 5000x3000 download of a sketch.
